role%2C%20can%20range%20much%20of%20the%20Pacific%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20long-range%20DF-27%20is%20said%20to%20be%20an%20option%20for%20both%20land-attack%20and%20anti-ship%20missions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20appears%20to%20have%20fielded%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussias-new-icbm-keeps-failing-leaving-older-and-inferior-missiles-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eintercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20DF-27%2C%20which%20can%20range%20the%20continental%20US%20and%2C%20unlike%20other%20ICBMs%2C%20serve%20a%20mix%20of%20missions%2C%20including%20targeting%20ships%2C%20a%20new%20Pentagon%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Defense's%20annual%20report%20on%20the%20Chinese%20military%2C%20the%20latest%20of%20which%20came%20out%20last%20week%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20the%20first%20public%20assessment%20that%20the%20missile%20is%20operational.%20The%20missile%20is%20said%20to%20have%20a%20land-attack%20and%20anti-ship%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latter%20role%20is%20unusual%20for%20an%20intercontinental-range%20ballistic%20missile%2C%20as%20is%20its%20conventional%20strike%20role%20documented%20in%20the%20new%20Pentagon%20report.%20ICBMs%20are%20primarily%20for%20nuclear%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%20offers%20little%20on%20the%20new%20missile%20beyond%20a%20map%20showing%20China's%20%26quot%3Bfielded%20conventional%20strike.%26quot%3B%20The%20DF-27%2C%20identified%20as%20an%20ICBM%20with%20a%20range%20of%205%2C000%20to%208%2C000%20km%2C%20shorter%20than%20some%20other%20systems%20built%20for%20strategic%20nuclear%20strike%2C%20is%20a%20new%20addition%20to%20that%20map%20showing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-pentagon-maps-show-the-reach-of-chinas-expanding-missile-force-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChinese%20missile%20ranges%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20range%20completely%20covers%20Hawaii%20and%20Alaska%2C%20and%20it%20also%20extends%20into%20parts%20of%20the%20continental%20US.%20The%20exact%20reach%20might%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20launch%20site%2C%20but%20broadly%2C%20the%20weapon%20puts%20naval%20forces%20and%20US%20military%20installations%20across%20the%20Pacific%20at%20risk%20in%20a%20new%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%26quot%3Blong-range%26quot%3B%20DF-27%20missile%20was%20first%20mentioned%20in%20the%202021%20Pentagon%20report.%20It%20said%20that%20indications%20on%20the%20range%20hinted%20at%20either%20an%20intercontinental-%20or%20intermediate-range%20missile.%20That%20uncertainty%20persisted%20until%20the%202025%20report%20identified%20it%20as%20an%20ICBM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20Pentagon%20report%20notably%20offered%20the%20most%20detail%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20DF-27%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bdeployed%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20Rocket%20Force.%20It%20added%20that%20this%20weapon%20likely%20has%20an%20option%20for%20an%20HGV%2C%20a%20hypersonic%20glide%20vehicle%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20well%20as%20conventional%20land-attack%2C%20conventional%20antiship%2C%20and%20nuclear%20capabilities.%26quot%3B%20The%202025%20report%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20put%20the%20weapon%20under%20%26quot%3Bfielded%20nuclear%20capabilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Missile%20Defense%20Advocacy%20Alliance%2C%20the%20DF-27%20carries%20potentially%20significant%20strategic%20implications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.missiledefenseadvocacy.org%2Fmissile-threat-and-proliferation%2Ftodays-missile-threat%2Fchina%2Fdf-27%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly%20assessment%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Chinese%20missile%20published%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20group%20cited%20a%20leaked%20intelligence%20briefing%20indicating%20the%20missile%20was%20tested%20in%20February%202023%20and%20warned%20that%20it%20could%20give%20China%20another%20means%20to%20hold%20targets%20at%20risk%20beyond%20the%20second%20island%20chain%2C%20with%20a%20high%20likelihood%20of%20being%20able%20to%20penetrate%20US%20ballistic-missile%20defenses%20and%20the%20potential%20to%20serve%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-chinas-df-26-missile-so-dangerous-for-us-military-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecarrier%20killer%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20not%20publicly%20commented%20on%20the%20DF-27%2C%20though%20local%20media%20have%20at%20times%20approached%20the%20topic%20indirectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221004%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20showing%20estimated%20ranges%20of%20Chinese%20missiles%20outside%20of%20the%20mainland%20and%20towards%20other%20regions.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6954140c64858d02d21789d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221088%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20estimated%20ranges%20of%20Chinese%20missiles%20across%20the%20region%20and%20towards%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Defense%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFielding%20the%20new%20DF-27%20makes%20China%20the%20first%20to%20have%20an%20operational%2C%20conventionally%20armed%20ICBM.%20The%20US%20and%20Russia%20have%20not%20fielded%20similar%20capabilities%3B%20however%2C%20both%20have%20been%20pursuing%20new%20intermediate-range%20capabilities%20since%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Intermediate-Range%20Nuclear%20Forces%20Treaty%2C%20which%20the%20US%20walked%20away%20from%20in%202019%20after%20accusing%20Russia%20of%20non-compliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DF-27%20is%20the%20latest%20example%20of%20China's%20efforts%20to%20develop%20and%20field%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-china-missile-problem-getting-worse-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evaried%2C%20flexible%20strike%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20potential%20conflict.%20The%20missile%20branch%20of%20its%20military%2C%20cal