Wisconsin%20since%201999.%3Cp%3ETim%20Gruber%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Walmart%2C%20the%20largest%20private%20employer%20in%20the%20US%2C%20about%2013.3%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20or%20over%20200%2C000%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20is%20over%2060%20years%20old%2C%20and%20more%20than%20300%2C000%20employees%20have%20a%20tenure%20of%20more%20than%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20be%20a%20great%20place%20to%20work%20during%20every%20stage%20of%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20come%20here%20for%20a%20first%20job%20or%20a%20second%20career%2C%20and%20we%20have%20associates%20from%2016%20to%20100.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20Magnuson%2C%2083%2C%20has%20worked%20as%20a%20yard%20driver%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretail-ceos-new-class-taking-the-reins-walmart-target-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWalmart%3C%2Fa%3E%20facility%20in%20Wisconsin%20since%201999.%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20transitioned%20to%20an%20asset%20protection%20position%2C%20where%20he%20monitors%20fire%20systems%20and%20recertifies%20employees%20who%20use%20certain%20equipment.%20Magnuson%20said%20he%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20savings%20to%20retire.%20He%20described%20the%20work%2C%20which%20pays%20low%20six%20figures%2C%20as%20fulfilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20reporting%20is%20part%20of%20Business%20Insider's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-we-learned-from-americas-oldest-workers-80-over-80-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E80%20over%2080%3C%2Fa%3E%20series%2C%20drawing%20on%20interviews%20with%20over%20300%20workers%2080%20years%20of%20age%20or%20older%2C%20their%20loved%20ones%2C%20and%20experts.%20These%20workers%20overall%20felt%20they%20were%20supported%20at%20work%20and%20that%20their%20employers%20appreciated%20their%20commitment%20and%20work%20ethic%2C%20while%20others%20said%20they%20were%20grateful%20to%20have%20robust%20health%20benefits%2C%20flexible%20work%20schedules%2C%20and%20remote%20work%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3ERuth%20Finkelstein%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20public%20health%20at%20Hunter%20College%2C%20said%20employers%20should%20provide%20mentorship%20and%20flexibility%20to%20workers%20of%20all%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20reach%20their%20peak%20earnings%20in%20their%2050s%20and%20then%20gradually%20decrease%20after%20that%20until%20they%20abruptly%20decrease%20after%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Finkelstein%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20have%20retirement%20security%20adequate%20to%20meet%20people's%20needs%20without%20them%20having%20to%20work%20for%20their%20whole%20lives%2C%20and%20we%20should%20have%20legislation%20that's%20much%20stronger%20than%20that%20against%20employment%20discrimination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3f10dc3-8c9f-485c-9d31-220921e61b01%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Disney%2C%20Starbucks%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20others%20support%20older%20workers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20biggest%20names%20in%20the%20retail%2C%20entertainment%2C%20and%20food%20sectors%20have%20proposed%20age-friendly%20policies%20and%20initiatives%20to%20support%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECVS%20Health%20has%20developed%20programs%20to%20attract%20mature%20workers%20and%20develop%20their%20skills.%20Many%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pack-disney-things-travel-brings-skips-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDisney%3C%2Fa%3E's%20employees%20are%20in%20their%20second%20or%20third%20career%2C%20said%20Tami%20Garcia%2C%20executive%20vice%20president%20of%20people%20and%20culture%20at%20Disney%20Experiences.%20The%20company%20gives%20out%20the%20Walt%20Disney%20Legacy%20Award%20and%20holds%20service%20anniversary%20ceremonies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20many%2C%20having%20a%20role%20at%20one%20of%20our%20Disney%20parks%20is%20a%20second%20or%20even%20third%20career%2C%20and%20we%20deeply%20value%20the%20experience%2C%20wisdom%2C%20and%20mentorship%20that%20can%20bring%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20celebrating%20milestone%20anniversaries%20%E2%80%94%20including%2050%2B%20years%20of%20service%20%E2%80%94%20to%20honoring%20those%20who%20embody%20Walt%20Disney's%20legacy%20through%20our%20recognition%20programs%2C%20we%20showcase%20respect%2C%20care%2C%20and%20appreciation%20for%20our%20Cast%20Members.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20have%20prioritized%20certain%20accommodations%2C%20such%20as%20flexible%20work%20schedules.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrian-niccol-starbucks-friends-cafe-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStarbucks%3C%2Fa%3E%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3BBack%20to%20Starbucks%26quot%3B%20strategy%20has%20invested%20over%20%24500%20million%20in%20operational%20improvements%20and%20the%20workplace%20experience%2C%20which%20could%20benefit%20older%20workers%20looking%20for%20more%20flexibility.%20The%20spokesperson%20said%20that%2085%25%20of%20employees%20receive%20their%20preferred%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllen%20Ernst%20Kossek%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Purdue%20University%20who%20studies%20work-life%20relationships%2C%20said%20companies%20should%20consider%20reducing%20the%20workloads%20of%20older%20employees%2C%20helping%20these%20workers%20adapt%20to%20new%20technologies%2C%20and%20finding%20ways%20to%20challenge%20age-related%20stereotypes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20stereotype%20that%20older%20workers%20are%20not%20as%20current%2C%20but%20just%20as%20you%20would%20train%20new%20workers%20or%20encourage%20people%20to%20get%20a%20certificate%2C%20they%20could%20adapt%20their%20strategies%20to%20look%20for%20people%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-simple-tip-for-breaking-into-ai-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20encourage%20people%20to%20keep%20their%20skills%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Kossek%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they've%20adopted%20certain%20benefits%2C%20such%20as%20greater%20access%20to%20medical%20care%2C%20which%20may%20help%20older%20workers%20stay%20healthy%20and%20avoid%20early%20retirement%20due%20to%20medical%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20be%20beneficial%20to%20both%20companies%20and%20their%20workers.%20Older%20workers%20can%20increase%20corporate%20healthcare%20costs%2C%20since%20the%20majority%20of%20people%20aged%2065%20and%20older%20have%20a%20chronic%20disease%2C%20said%20Dr.%20Susan%20Mueller%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20health%20equity%20and%20well-being%20at%20global%20advisory%20firm%20WTW.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalgreens%20offers%20benefits%20for%20%26quot%3Bbalancing%20work%20with%20caregiving%20responsibilities%2C%20preparing%20for%20retirement%2C%20or%20seeking%20proactive%20health%20and%20financial%20well-being%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20said.%20UnitedHealth%20Group%20provides%20legal%20services%20for%20estate%20planning%20and%20family%20law%2C%20and%20supports%20workers%20navigating%20menopause%20or%20cancer%20diagnoses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Google%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20gives%20employees%20access%20to%20financial%20coaching%20for%20retirement%20and%20personalized%20assistance%20for%20managing%20caregiving.%20The%20company%20offers%20benefits%20such%20as%20cancer%20testing%20and%20support%2C%20no-cost%20medical%20second%20opinions%2C%20and%20no-cost%20virtual%20primary%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20emphasized%20the%20company's%20paid%20time%20off%20for%20caregiving%20for%20loved%20ones%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-american-workers-health-issues-challenges-disabilities-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eserious%20illness%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20wraparound%20care%20to%20support%20healthy%20aging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFedEx%20has%20launched%20comprehensive%20medical%20benefits%20and%20support%20networks%2C%20such%20as%20its%20Choose%20Well%20Care%20Connect%20advocacy%20program%2C%20which%20guides%20members%20through%20life-altering%20diagnoses.%20FedEx%20launched%20a%20Fast%20Pass%20in%20certain%20markets%20to%20guarantee%20members%20a%20primary%20care%20appointment%20within%2010%20days%20or%20less.%20The%20company's%20corporate%20responsibility%20report%20notes%20that%20FedEx%20is%20testing%20home%20health%20capabilities%20in%20areas%20with%20limited%20healthcare%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Thomas%20Magnuson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69556ae264858d02d2179b55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThomas%20Magnuson%20said%20there%20aren't%20too%20many%20people%20doing%20the%20type%20of%20work%20he%20does%20in%20their%2080s.%3Cp%3ETim%20Gruber%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281f814de-d6a1-4476-ada3-f17b657ca2ed%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompanies%20have%20more%20work%20to%20do%2C%20experts%20say%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETopics%20like%20AI%20and%20climate%20change%20are%20garnering%20more%20attention%20in%20corporate%20America%20than%20the%20aging%20workforce%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Insider%20analysis%20of%20earnings%20calls%2C%2010-Ks%2C%20and%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20concern%20to%20some%20experts%20on%20aging%2C%20who%20say%20companies%20need%20to%20be%20doing%20more%20to%20prepare%20for%20shifting%20demographics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMueller%20said%20companies%20should%20develop%20programs%20that%20control%20costs%20for%20employees%20needing%20medical%20assistance%3B%20establish%20internal%20guidelines%20to%20help%20employees%20navigate%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-vc-predictions-2026-more-ai-acquisitions-few-ipos-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehealthcare%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20add%20virtual%20primary%20care%3B%20and%20hire%20external%20companies%20specializing%20in%20common%20medical%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMadonna%20Harrington%20Meyer%2C%20a%20sociology%20professor%20at%20Syracuse%20University%2C%20said%20that%20during%20economically%20hard%20times%2C%20older%20workers%20are%20often%20the%20first%20to%20be%20laid%20off%20and%20the%20last%20to%20be%20rehired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarrington%20Meyer%20said%20companies%20should%20focus%20on%20accessibility%20and%20safety.%20They%20should%20arrange%20parking%20spots%20near%20office%20entrances%2C%20ensure%20good%20lighting%20and%20soundproofing%20for%20sensory%20needs%2C%20and%20maintain%20functional%20elevators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraham%20Pearce%2C%20global%20defined%20benefit%20segment%20leader%20at%20the%20consulting%20firm%20Mercer%2C%20said%20some%20companies%20will%20need%20to%20confront%20an%26quot%3Bunconscious%20bias%26quot%3B%20against%20older%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20often%20seen%20as%20less%20adaptable%20or%20more%20prone%20to%20illness.%20Progress%20may%20require%20legislative%20action%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22949f7369-37ce-499b-b581-105496855dc7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegislative%20action%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bipartisan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F119th-congress%2Fhouse-bill%2F5514%2Ftext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProtect%20Older%20Job%20Applicants%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20introduced%20in%20September%20to%20prohibit%20age-based%20applicant%20sorting%20for%20employers%2C%20ensure%20%26quot%3Bdisparate%20impact%26quot%3B%20protections%20apply%20to%20employees%20and%20applicants%2C%20and%20require%20government%20oversight%20on%20age%20discrimination%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Bobby%20Scott%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Virginia%20who%20co-led%20the%20bill%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20hopes%20age%20discrimination%20will%20be%20considered%20%26quot%3Bas%20illegal%20as%20discrimination%20based%20on%20race%2C%20color%2C%20creed%2C%20national%20origin%2C%20or%20sex.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20if%20more%20people%20have%20employment%20opportunities%20later%20in%20life%2C%20it%20could%20stimulate%20the%20economy%20and%20help%20people%20age%20with%20dignity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20Sen.%20Kirsten%20Gillibrand%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20New%20York%2C%20introduced%20the%20bipartisan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gillibrand.senate.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress%2Frelease%2Fsenator-gillibrand-introduces-bipartisan-legislation-to-allow-victims-of-age-discrimination-to-seek-justice-and-accountability%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProtecting%20Older%20Americans%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20end%20forced%20arbitration%20clauses%20prohibiting%20victims%20of%20age%20discrimination%20from%20suing%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20forced%20arbitration%20often%20discriminates%20against%20the%20plaintiff%2C%20and%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20older%20Americans%2C%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20resources%20to%20mount%20significant%20litigations%20against%20an%20employer%20who%20discriminates%20against%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Gillibrand%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20if%20you%20have%20the%20right%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20go%20to%20a%20trial%20and%20to%20be%20judged%20by%20your%20peers%2C%20older%20Americans%20would%20do%20better%20in%20these%20lawsuits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Sen.%20Tammy%20Baldwin%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Wisconsin%2C%20said%20that%20the%20separate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F119th-congress%2Fhouse-bill%2F3522%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProtecting%20Older%20Workers%20Against%20Discrimination%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20help%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20for%20older%20workers%20and%20combat%20age%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20do%20more%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20every%20American%20can%20plan%20and%20save%20for%20a%20secure%20retirement%2C%20but%20as%20more%20and%20more%20of%20our%20neighbors%20are%20forced%20to%20work%20later%20in%20life%20just%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%2C%20we%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20everyone%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20their%20age%20%E2%80%94%20has%20protections%20and%20dignity%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%26quot%3B%20Baldwin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faging-workforce-retirement-google-microsoft-walmart-starbucks-corporate-america-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767207315000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69556a6f832e0ef1ead70659%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faging-workforce-retirement-google-microsoft-walmart-starbucks-corporate-america-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Business%20Insider%20reached%20out%20to%20more%20than%2075%20major%20employers%2C%20including%20Walmart%20and%20Google%2C%20about%20their%20efforts%20to%20support%20aging%20workers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40businessinsider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faging-workforce-retirement-google-microsoft-walmart-starbucks-corporate-america-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fireworks%2C%20drums%20and%20light%20shows%3A%20How%20the%20world%20is%20welcoming%202026%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767206475000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2Fe8dd%2Flive%2F0cef03a0-e678-11f0-a8dc-93c15fe68710.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%2